name: NEO Kuchisake
description:
This artwork is taken from the concept of a Japanese ghost story, which is combined with the concept of the future, cyberpunk and scifi, to make it look even more different.

Kuchisake-onna (口裂け女, "Slit-Mouthed Woman") is a malevolent figure in Japanese urban legends and folklore. Described as the malicious spirit, or onryō, of a woman, she partially covers her face with a mask.
